The paper deals with the analysis of strings and their properties, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The study of maximal repetitions and their exponents involves combinatorial and algorithmic aspects, which are also relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the linear relationship between the length of the word and the number of maximal repetitions, which is a topic of interest in formal languages (cs.FL). The authors use information theory to analyze the properties of maximal repetitions, which is relevant to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the statistical properties of maximal repetitions, which is a topic of interest in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG).
